le=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 17, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104jzq1665702665465.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/jzq1665702665465.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/jzq1665702665465.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"jzq1665702665465\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      trigger getFocus (Form)\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Interactive trigger that responds to the form getting focus.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"jzq1665702665465__section_w87ab1b7b1_w88ab1b7_w89ab1\">\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"jzq1665702665465__table_d14486e1_d14487e1_d14488e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Declaration:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">trigger getFocus</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Applies to:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"euw1665702582150.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/euw1665702582150.html\" title=\"A Form is a stateful presentation Component that enables users to view and modify data in a Windows or character mode application.\">Form</a>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Activation:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Activated by the form getting focus as a result of user actions or ProcScript commands.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Default behavior:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n None\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Behavior upon completion:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n None\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"jzq1665702665465__section_w90ab1b7b3_w91ab1b7_w92ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d239761e129\">\n                       \n Description\n </h2>\n<div class=\"note caution note_caution\" id=\"jzq1665702665465__note_w96ab1b7b3b3_w97ab1b7b3_w98ab1b7_w99ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">CAUTION:</span> Do not use the\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">getFocus</code> trigger to change focus. For example, you should not use\n            ProcScript instructions such as <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">setformfocus</span> or\n               <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$prompt</span>, display a dialog box, or activate another component\n            instance in this trigger.</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"jzq1665702665465__section_w93ab1b7b5_w94ab1b7_w95ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d239761e147\">\n                       \n Trigger Activation\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jzq1665702665465__p_d117206e1_d117207e1_d117208e1\">The getFocus trigger can be activated in several ways:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"jzq1665702665465__li_d44597e1_d44598e1_d44599e1\">When a mouse click positions the cursor in the current form (whether or not it is minimized), after the loseFocus trigger of the previous form completes successfully.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"jzq1665702665465__li_d44600e1_d44601e1_d44602e1\">When a form receives focus after a form that previously had focus stops, for example, following ^ACCEPT, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">return</span>, and so on. (This occurs even if the form receiving focus is minimized.)\n </li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"jzq1665702665465__section_exk_3sg_fcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d239761e168\">Example: Communicating with a Parent Instance</h2>\n<div class=\"div\">\n<p class=\"p\">The following example sends a message to the parent form when the\n               current form get focus:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"jzq1665702665465__pre_gyt_3sg_fcc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">trigger getFocus\n if ($instanceparent != \"\")\n postmessage $instanceparent, \"GETTING FOCUS\", $instancename\n endif\nend; getFocus</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/oxi1665702665543.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>trigger loseFocus (Form)</a><p>ProcScript module that responds to the form losing focus. It can be used to verify the data to ensure that it is complete or correct.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tod1665702665614.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>setformfocus</a><p>Set the focus to the specified component instance.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529114\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529114\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "trigger getFocus (Form) Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 17, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 trigger getFocus (Form) Interactive trigger that responds to the form getting focus. Declaration: trigger getFocus Applies to: Form Activation: Activated by the form getting focus as a result of user actions or ProcScript commands. Default behavior: None Behavior upon completion: None Description CAUTION: Do not use the getFocus trigger to change focus. For example, you should not use ProcScript instructions such as setformfocus or $prompt , display a dialog box, or activate another component instance in this trigger. Trigger Activation The getFocus trigger can be activated in several ways: When a mouse click positions the cursor in the current form (whether or not it is minimized), after the loseFocus trigger of the previous form completes successfully. When a form receives focus after a form that previously had focus stops, for example, following ^ACCEPT, return , and so on. (This occurs even if the form receiving focus is minimized.) Example: Communicating with a Parent Instance The following example sends a message to the parent form when the current form get focus: trigger getFocus if ($instanceparent != \"\") postmessage $instanceparent, \"GETTING FOCUS\", $instancename endif end; getFocus Copy Related Links trigger loseFocus (Form) ProcScript module that responds to the form losing focus. It can be used to verify the data to ensure that it is complete or correct. setformfocus Set the focus to the specified component instance. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}